{"key":"processedPost-12261088","value":{"id":12261088,"first":12002751,"last":26810206,"when":1269442191,"utime":"03/24/10 05:49 PM","content":"We do something similar to this with shiitake.&nbsp; After full colonization, the 5 pound blocks are removed from the filter patch bags and allowed to dry out on a shelf in a dry room for three weeks.&nbsp; At the end of the drying/browning period, the substrates are soaked 24 hours and put into fruiting conditions.&nbsp; This results in better pinsets and more finished product than the traditional method of introducing to fruiting without the drying cycle.<br /><br />It also mimics nature in that the substrate dries out during the long hot summer, and then fruits when the fall rains come.<br /><br />Nice thread.&nbsp; Thanks for posting.<br />RR","title":"Re: How LM makes his cakes"}}